<br>
I think Verant customer service does some things well (given the compromise between the high needs for service and the budge $10/month allows where they have to use guides), and some things very badly that need improvement.<br>
<br>
But the difference is, I can say which specific things I think need improvement; they're reasonable issues, such as the fact that they announced a policy that you reporting your account hacked will get it banned even if you were not at fault - which may be a small percentage of times, but nonetheless it's wrong.<br>
<br>
You on the other hand right nonsense here:<br>
<br>
&quot;Rule 1: There are no bugs.&quot;<br>
Verant admits they have bugs. You are wrong.<br>
<br>
&quot;Rule 2: If you report a bug you are either lieing, a cheater, or a hacker. So reporting a bug means we ban you.&quot;<br>
Verant encourages the reporting of bugs, and they fix many from customer reports. Wrong again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Rule 3: We are not responsible for any of our coding, we are perfect and never make mistakes and being the al powerful wizard of oz, err Verant we can do as we please. &quot;<br>
Verant says they are responsible for their coding. They admit they aren't perfect.<br>
<br>
The real problem are the few customers who just throw mud no matter what and ruin the Verant-customer relationship, like your post. It's why they ended the discussion on their message forums.<br>
<br>
Try not to throw temper tantrums at Verant - it won't help anyone.<br>
