<br>
Thank you for your email. While I wholeheartedly understand<br>
the frustration in losing items, as I explained in game, your corpse decayed while your account was logged on. Please note that the corpse timer will continue to count down at the online rate if you are online with any character on the account. I am sorry to be the barer of bad news but as per our reimbursement policy posted at everquest.station.sony.co.../index.jsp we are unable to restore your corpse. If you have any further questions please feel free to email me.<br>
<br>
<br>
And again: <br>
He camped out 1 or 2 hours after the death. (Yes, he camped, he didn't /q)<br>
He logged on 2 days later with a Necro to summon his corpse (he didn't go to chat or played a twink, this was the 1st time, he logged the account back on), Kirak was even expecting to be able to get the exp back with a rez. No corpse there and the GM tells him, it decayed exactly 24 hours after the death...<br>
<br>
Ok, the account stayed online, though Kirak camped out. A problem of his ISP? Hard to believe. <br>
A problem at Verant? Gotcha !<br>
<br>
We had many situations, where the CS didn't help us a bit. This one is one too much. What the hell do they loose, if they restore his character? He didn't die in VP or some zone like that, he died in the Tower of Frozen Shadows. Quite easy to get his corpse out of that zone. He justed camped after he died, because it was late and he had to work the next day.<br>
<br>
I am sick of all this &quot;the player is guilty, unless he (or she) can proof he isn't&quot; stuff.<br>
<br>
We are a small guild. We are more like a family. We meet each other 2 or 3 times in a year. Kirak is always willing to help others. If such a nice person looses everything due to a problem, he has no influence upon, it is a horrible situation for our whole guild. Sure we could get his stuff again quite fast, but that isn't the point. He cancelled his account due to the fact, that he got NO HELP AT ALL from the Verant-CS. He is tired. So are we as a guild.<br>
<br>
We still have some things, we will try. If all that doesn't help, I am afraid, you won't see many &quot;Ringers&quot; in EQ anymore.<br>
